0Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20had%20earlier%20said%20that%20India%20has%20been%20provided%20with%20all%20the%20necessary%20information%20and%20documentation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20was%20later%20asked%20by%20a%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Magazine%3C%2Fem%3E%20journalist%20about%20whether%20he%20was%20provided%20evidence%20on%20the%20matter%20by%20the%20Canadian%20government%2C%20specifically%20evidence%20of%20intercepted%20communications%20(which%20Canada%20has%20said%20is%20what%20links%20the%20matter%20to%20the%20Indian%20government).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAre%20you%20saying%20that%20the%20Canadians%20gave%20us%20documents%3F%E2%80%9D%20Jaishankar%20said.%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20asking%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20reporter%20replied%2C%20and%20Jaishankar%20was%20then%20asked%20again%20if%20a%20document%20regarding%20India%E2%80%99s%20intercepted%20diplomatic%20communications%20had%20been%20provided.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20said%20that%20if%20somebody%20gives%20us%20specific%20or%20relevant%20information%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20prepared%20to%20look%20at%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jaishankar%20responded.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20on%20whether%20India%20had%20received%20evidence%20regarding%20intercepted%20communications%20was%20posed%20again%2C%20to%20which%20Jaishankar%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20I%20had%2C%20would%20I%20not%20be%20looking%20at%20it%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20minister%20was%20again%20asked%20for%20a%20%E2%80%98yes%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98no%E2%80%99%20on%20whether%20India%20had%20received%20such%20documentation%2C%20at%20which%20point%20Juster%20intervened.%20Jaishankar%20then%20refused%20to%20entertain%20a%20second%20question%20from%20the%20same%20journalist.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20also%20refused%20to%20answer%20a%20separate%20question%20on%20information%20that%20had%20reportedly%20been%20shared%20between%20the%20Five%20Eyes%20on%20Nijjar%E2%80%99s%20killing%2C%20as%20well%20as%20threat%20perceptions%20that%20the%20FBI%20has%20reportedly%20told%20US-based%20Sikhs%20about.%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20not%20part%20of%20the%20Five%20Eyes%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20certainly%20not%20part%20of%20the%20FBI%2C%20so%20I%20think%20you%E2%80%99re%20asking%20the%20wrong%20person%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20first%20talking%20about%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20allegations%2C%20Jaishankar%20alleged%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cimportant%20context%E2%80%9D%20was%20that%20Canada%20had%20a%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20permissive%E2%80%9D%20environment%20for%20secessionist%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECanada%20had%20seen%20significant%20amounts%20of%20%E2%80%9Corganised%20crime%20relating%20to%20secessionist%20forces%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20Jaishankar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20actually%20been%20badgering%20the%20Canadians%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20given%20them%20a%20lot%20of%20information%20about%20organised%20crime%20leadership%2C%20which%20operates%20out%20of%20Canada.%20%E2%80%A6There%20are%20a%20large%20number%20of%20extradition%20requests.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20first%20time%20Jaishankar%20addressed%20the%20Canada%20matter%20directly%20during%20his%20trip%20to%20the%20US.%20While%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fjab-west-jaishankar-political-convenience-response-terrorism-canada%5C%22%3Espeaking%20at%20the%20United%20Nations%20General%20Assembly%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20had%20not%20named%20Canada%20but%20buttressed%20that%20terrorism%20and%20extremism%20cannot%20be%20fought%20as%20per%20%E2%80%9Cpolitical%20convenience%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20respect%20for%20territorial%20integrity%20cannot%20be%20an%20exercise%20in%20%E2%80%9Ccherry-picking%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20%E2%80%98democratic%20backsliding%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20by%20a%20journalist%20whether%20India%20was%20worried%20about%20the%20perceptions%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdemocratic%20backsliding%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20country%2C%20as%20detailed%20by%20various%20international%20reports%2C%20Jaishankar%20said%20that%20reports%20like%20this%20were%20in%20fact%20%E2%80%9Criddled%20with%20inaccuracies%E2%80%9D.%20This%20is%20in%20line%20with%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20previous%20denials%20of%20such%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%E2%80%99s%20an%20ideological%20agenda%20out%20there.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20why%20that%E2%80%99s%20hard%20to%20understand%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jaishankar%20said%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EForeign%20Affairs%3C%2Fem%3E%20journalist%20who%20had%20posed%20the%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20India-Russia%20and%20India-China%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20interaction%2C%20Jaishankar%20said%20that%20the%20India-Russia%20relationship%20is%20very%20stable%20and%20both%20countries%20made%20efforts%20to%20ensure%20it%20remained%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20had%20been%20good%20and%20bad%20periods%20in%20the%20US-Russia%2C%20Russia-China%20and%20Europe-Russia%20relationships%20over%20the%20last%2070%20years%2C%20but%20India%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20Russia%20had%20been%20%E2%80%9Cvery%2C%20very%2C%20steady%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20said%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Findia-takes-great-care-ensuring-steady-ties-with-russia-are-in-good-shape-eam-jaishankar%2Farticle67350879.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20global%20powers%20based%20out%20of%20Asia%2C%20India%20and%20Russia%20understood%20the%20importance%20of%20getting%20along%20with%20each%20other%2C%20Jaishankar%20continued.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20so%20we%20take%20great%20care%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20relationship%20is%20working.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20was%20answering%20a%20question%20on%20whether%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20proximity%20to%20China%20could%20affect%20the%20India-Russia%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20situation%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Russia%20has%20been%20looking%20more%20and%20more%20to%20building%20relationships%20in%20Asia%2C%20the%20minister%20continued.%20%E2%80%9CI%20would%20actually%20predict%20that%20Russia%20would%20make%20very%20strenuous%20efforts%20to%20build%20alternative%20relationships%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20which%20would%20be%20in%20Asia%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20India%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20China%2C%20Jaishankar%20said%20the%20two%20countries%20have%20been%20through%20various%20cycles%20and%20it%20has%20never%20been%20easy.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20the%20ambassador%20in%202009%2C%20right%20after%20the%20global%20financial%20crisis%2C%20till%202013.%20I%20saw%20the%20change%20of%20guard%20in%20China%2C%20and%20then%20I%20came%20to%20the%20US.%20It%20has%20never%20been%20an%20easy%20relationship.%20It%20always%20had%20its%20share%20of%20problems%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findo-china-relationship-has-never-been-an-easy-s-jaishankar-4427094%5C%22%3EANI%3C%2Fa%3E%20quoted%20him%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20a%20history%20of%20conflict%2C%20though%2C%20he%20said%20there%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20been%20a%20military%20or%20combat%20fatality%20on%20the%20border%20since%201975.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20had%20a%20war%20in%201962%2C%20it%20had%20military%20incidents%20after%20that.%20But%20after%201975%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20never%20been%20a%20military%2C%20a%20combat%20fatality%20on%20the%20border%2C%E2%80%9D%20ANI%20quoted%20Jaishankar%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20claiming%20there%20had%20been%20no%20%E2%80%9Ccombat%20fatality%E2%80%9D%20since%201975%2C%20Jaishankar%20did%20not%20make%20a%20reference%20to%20the%202020%20clash%20at%20Galwan%20Valley%2C%20which%20led%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Findian-army-officers-killed-china-galwan-valley%5C%22%3Edeath%20of%20at%20least%2020%20Indian%20Army%20jawans%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20he%20did%20s