%A8%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BC%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%AC%20%E0%A4%86%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%82%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESimpletons%20don%E2%80%99t%20seem%20to%20understand%20this%20truth%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUntil%20hearts%20do%20not%20turn%2C%20revolutions%20remain%20impossible%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20word%20for%20revolution%20in%20this%20couplet%20is%20%3Cem%3Einquilab%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20word%20many%20of%20you%20are%20familiar%20with.%20A%20word%20perhaps%20misused%2C%20often%20misunderstood%2C%20sometimes%20overused%20and%20nearly%20always%20something%20that%20could%20get%20you%20into%20trouble.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20word%20%3Cem%3Einquilab%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20from%20the%20Arabic%20word%20%3Cem%3Eqalb%3C%2Fem%3E%20which%20means%20heart%20and%20can%20sometimes%20mean%20the%20intellect.%20The%20heart%2C%20and%20not%20the%20brain%2C%20as%20the%20seat%20of%20intellect%20opens%20up%20a%20sea%20of%20possibilities%20in%20and%20of%20itself%20but%20let%20me%20not%20digress.%20The%20conjugated%20form%20of%20%3Cem%3Eqalb%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20derive%20the%20word%20%3Cem%3Einquilab%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20means%20to%20return%20or%20to%20restore.%20Any%20change%20must%20begin%20in%20the%20heart%3A%20the%20heart%2C%20that%20illusive%20seat%20of%20love%20in%20most%20spiritual%20traditions.%20But%20this%20love%2C%20while%20lying%20at%20our%20core%2C%20remains%20hidden%2C%20waiting%20for%20us%20to%20approach%20it%2C%20to%20nourish%20it%2C%20to%20let%20it%20guide%20us.%20We%20must%20not%20forget%2C%20as%20Brother%20Cornel%20West%20says%2C%20that%20justice%20is%20what%20love%20looks%20like%20in%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20most%20of%20us%20remain%20guided%20by%20our%20baser%20senses%2C%20for%20no%20fault%20of%20our%20own.%20From%20a%20young%20age%2C%20we%20are%20taught%20saying%20%E2%80%9Cno%E2%80%9D%20is%20inconvenient%2C%20unacceptable%20and%20sometimes%20downright%20dangerous.%20Young%20parents%20are%20often%20most%20frustrated%20when%20their%20toddler%20discovers%20the%20word%20%3Cem%3Eno%3C%2Fem%3E.%20This%20%3Cem%3Eno%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20development%20of%20self-awareness%20and%20autonomy.%20It%20is%20an%20unconscious%20test%20of%20the%20authority%20of%20the%20parents%20and%20eventually%2C%20it%20transforms%20into%20trust%20and%20cooperation.%20In%20most%20healthy%20relationships%2C%20the%20child%20realises%2C%20often%20unconsciously%2C%20that%20the%20parent%E2%80%99s%20concerns%20come%20out%20of%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESadly%2C%20however%2C%20most%20societies%20are%20not%20formed%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20mutual%20love%20and%20trust%20but%20self-interest.%20Therefore%2C%20all%20structures%20in%20societies%20need%20to%20be%20viewed%20through%20a%20critical%20lens.%20The%20self-interest%20of%20feudals%20around%20the%20world%20in%20the%2012th%20century%20is%20more%20obvious%20to%20some%20than%20the%20self-interest%20of%20economic%20elites%20today%2C%20veiled%20by%20dreams%20of%20progress%2C%20hidden%20behind%20illusions%20of%20hope%20and%20obscured%20by%20the%20mirage%20of%20merit.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESelf-interest%20is%20inevitably%20accompanied%20by%20and%20preserved%20through%20violence.%20If%20you%20read%20the%20origin%20stories%20of%20the%20world%2C%20you%20will%20realise%20the%20origins%20of%20religions%2C%20politics%20and%20history%20have%20always%20been%20tethered%20to%20violent%20fratricide%2C%20or%20%E2%80%98crime%E2%80%99%20as%20Hannah%20Arendt%20says.%20Whether%20Cain%20and%20Abel%20or%20the%20%3Cem%3EKauravas%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20%3Cem%3EPandavas%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20origin%20stories%20we%20tell%20future%20generations%20is%20often%20marked%20by%20bloodshed%2C%20not%20of%20distant%20others%20but%20of%20relatives%20and%20kinsmen.%20Even%20in%20Karbala%2C%20on%20one%20side%20there%20was%20the%20Prophet%E2%80%99s%20grandson%20Hussain%2C%20on%20the%20other%20side%20was%20not%20some%20distant%20other%20or%20some%20foreigner%20but%20kinsmen.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20beginning%20of%20our%20country%E2%80%99s%20history%20too%20is%20soaked%20in%20the%20blood%20of%20neighbours%20and%20brothers%20and%20sisters%20and%20not%20in%20the%20blood%20of%20the%20British%20who%20were%20being%20thrown%20out!%20This%20intimate%20enmity%20is%20what%20the%20powerful%20and%20the%20wealthy%20have%20always%20taken%20advantage%20of.%20The%20easiest%20way%20to%20control%20people%20is%20to%20make%20them%20afraid%20%3Cem%3Eof%3C%2Fem%3E%20themselves%20and%20%3Cem%3Efor%3C%2Fem%3E%20themselves.%20When%20we%20hate%20others%2C%20we%20are%20afraid%20of%20the%20darkness%20within%20ourselves%2C%20so%20we%20project%20it%20onto%20others.%20For%20what%20is%20hate%3F%20Nothing%20but%20our%20own%20sense%20of%20helplessness%2C%20powerlessness%2C%20inadequacy%20and%20shame%20for%20which%20we%20compensate%20by%20dehumanising%20someone%20else.%20Fundamentally%20humans%20haven%E2%80%99t%20changed%20much.%20Our%20conditions%20have%20changed%20and%20we%20have%20become%20better%20at%20obfuscating%20and%20obscuring%20the%20raw%20and%20brutal%20reality%20of%20power.%20These%20obfuscations%20operate%20at%20the%20social%20level%2C%20but%20also%20at%20the%20individual%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EToday%20more%20than%20ever%20before%20these%20distortions%20and%20distractions%20are%20made%20easier%20by%20virtual%20reality%20and%20technology%20which%20cloud%20our%20sense%20of%20self%2C%20make%20us%20less%20wary%2C%20less%20alert%20and%20more%20self-centred.%20In%20a%20sense%2C%20social%20media%20also%20reduces%20our%20ability%20to%20say%20no%2C%20albeit%20to%20ourselves.%20However%2C%20the%20challenges%20human%20beings%20faced%20millennia%20ago%20are%20not%20so%20different%20from%20the%20challenges%20we%20face%20today.%20Greed%2C%20hate%2C%20lust%2C%20anger%2C%20arrogance%20and%20envy%20are%20some%20of%20the%20things%20which%20the%20saints%20and%20prophets%20of%20ancient%20times%20warned%20us%20about.%20Their%20voices%20still%20echo%20among%20us%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EToday%20we%20see%20precisely%20these%20emotions%20are%20amplified%20to%20make%20the%20attention%20economy%20what%20it%20is.%20In%20a%20sense%2C%20the%20challenge%20put%20forward%20by%20Krishna%20Ji%20in%20the%20Gita%20in%20chapter%206%20%3Cem%3Eshlok%3C%2Fem%3E%205%20could%20not%20be%20more%20relevant.%20He%20asks%20us%20to%20elevate%20our%20mind%20and%20therefore%20elevate%20our%20self%20%E2%80%94%20the%20mind%20and%20the%20self%2C%20both%20referred%20to%20as%20%3Cem%3Eaatma%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3Eshlok%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20can%20be%20both%20friend%20and%20foe.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E0%A4%89%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A7%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%20%E0%A5%A4%20%E0%A4%86%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%88%E0%A4%B5%20%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8B%20%E0%A4%AC%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A7%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%88%E0%A4%B5%20%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AA%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%83%20%E0%A5%A5%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20true%20Yogi%20or%20Yogini%20is%20she%20who%20can%20feel%20the%20suffering%20and%20the%20happiness%20of%20others%20in%20equal%20measure%20and%20treats%20all%20living%20things%2C%20and%20I%20repeat%20%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eall%20living%20things%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20with%20equity%20and%20compassion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E0%A4%86%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%8C%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A8%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%B6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BF%20%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%8B%E0%A4%BD%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%9C%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%A8%20%7C%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%96%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%BF%20%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%81%3A%E0%A4%96%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%B8%20%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%8B%E0%A4%97%E0%A5%80%20%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%8B%20%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%A4%3A%20%E0%A5%A5%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESadly%20those%20who%20style%20themselves%20as%20Yogis%20have%20perhaps%20not%20read%20this%20in%20chapter%206%20verse%2032%20of%20the%20Gita.%20So%2C%20the%20real%20%3Cem%3Einquilab%3C%2Fem%3E%20then%20is%20the%20transformation%20of%20the%20heart.%20That%20is%20the%20real%20revolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%D9%85%D8%AA%20%D8%B3%DB%81%D9%84%20%DB%81%D9%85%DB%8C%DA%BA%20%D8%AC%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%88%20%D9%BE%DA%BE%D8%B1%D8%AA%D8%A7%20%DB%81%DB%92%20%D9%81%D9%84%DA%A9%20%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%88%DA%BA%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%D8%AA%D8%A8%20%D8%AE%D8%A7%DA%A9%20%DA%A9%DB%92%20%D9%BE%D8%B1%D8%AF%DB%92%20%D8%B3%DB%92%20%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%86%20%D9%86%DA%A9%D9%84%D8%AA%DB%92%20%DB%81%DB%8C%DA%BA%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMat%20sahal%20humen%20jaano%2C%20phirta%20hai%20falak%20barson%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPhir%20khaak%20ke%20purde%20se%2C%20insaan%20nikalta%20hai%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%A4%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%B2%20%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8B%20%E0%A4%AB%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%88%20%E0%A4%AB%E0%A4%BC%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%95%20%E0%A4%AC%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%8B%E0%A4%82%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%AC%20%E0%A4%96%E0%A4%BC%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%95%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%87%E0%A4%82%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%20%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%88%E0%A4%82%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20think%20it%20easy%2C%20for%20the%20skies%20revolve%20for%20an%20eternity%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThen%2C%20from%20the%20curtain%20of%20dust%2C%20does%20a%20human%20eventually%20emerge%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20an%20%3Cem%3Einsaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20perhaps%20the%20most%20difficult%20task%20of%20all.%20Perhaps%20it%20would%20be%20too%20much%20to%20claim%20Mir%20Taqi%20Mir%20was%20onto%20evolution%20in%2018th%20century%20Delhi%2C%20but%20he%20certainly%20was%20aware%20it%20takes%20years%2C%20literally%20many%20revolutions%20of%20the%20earth%2C%20for%20us%20to%20wipe%20away%20the%20dust%20that%20prevents%20us%20from%20being%20fully%20realised%20human%20beings.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20English%20and%20Hindi%2C%20the%20word%20revolution%20also%20alludes%20to%20celestial%20motion%2C%20the%20same%20revolving%20Mir%20alluded%20to%20in%20the%20couplet%20I%20just%20read%2C%20The%20English%20word%20%E2%80%98revolution%E2%80%99%20comes%20from%20the%20Latin%20root%20%3Cem%3Erevolvo%3C%2Fem%3E%20which%20means%20%E2%80%98to%20return%E2%80%99%2C%20among%20other%20things.%20The%20Hindi%20word%20%3Cem%3Ekranti%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20roots%20in%20Sanskrit%20connoting%20proceeding%2C%20surpassing%20and%20even%20overcoming.%20The%20Chinese%20equivalent%2C%20%3Cem%3Eg%C3%A9m%C3%ACng%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20means%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20%E2%80%98the%20removal%20of%20heaven%E2%80%99s%20mandate%E2%80%99.%20The%20fact%20remains%3A%20the%20modern%20definition%20of%20revolution%20as%20an%20event%20or%20series%20of%20events%20connoting%20complete%20or%20radical%20change%20is%20only%20one%20way%20to%20study%20revolutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENo%20doubt%2C%20during%20your%20journey%20in%20Ashoka%2C%20you%20will%20come%20across%20the%20Glorious%20Revolution%20in%20England%2C%20The%20American%20Revolution%2C%20the%20Haitian%20Revolution%2C%20the%20French%20Revolution%2C%20the%201848%20revolutions%2C%20the%20Republican%20Revolution%20of%201911%20in%20China%2C%20the%20Bolshevik%20Revolution%20of%201917%2C%20the%20Bolivian%20Revolution%20of%201952%2C%20the%20Iranian%20Revolution%20of%201979%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20the%20various%20colour%20revolutions%20as%20well%20as%20the%20revolutions%20we%20talk%20of%20in%20agriculture%2C%20science%2C%20industry%20or%20technology.%20Many%20of%20these%20political%20revolutions%2C%20despite%20their%20promises%2C%20end%20in%20tyranny%20and%20yet%20people%20continue%20to%20hope%20and%20imagine%20a%20better%20world!%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20all%20of%20these%20revolutions%20and%20regardless%20of%20whether%20we%20understand%20them%20to%20be%20successful%20or%20not%2C%20there%20is%20one%20thing%20that%20connects%20all%20of%20them%20%E2%80%93%20they%20began%20with%20%3Cem%3Eno%3C%2Fem%3E.%20They%20began%20with%20a%20small%20number%20of%20people%2C%20or%20often%20even%20just%20individuals%2C%20who%20refused%20to%20accept%20the%20status%20quo%2C%20refused%20to%20accept%20the%20existing%20order%20of%20things.%20And%20of%20course%2C%20this%20journey%20of%20saying%20%E2%80%98NO!%E2%80%99%20began%20with%20asking%20questions.%20It%20has%20never%20been%20easy%20to%20ask%20questions%20in%20human%20history.%20Those%20who%20have%20questioned%20have%20been%20persecuted%2C%20hounded%2C%20punished%20and%20even%20killed.%20Science%20has%20progressed%20because%20of%20the%20courage%20and%20strength%20people%20had%20to%20say%20no.%20Philosophical%20movements%20and%20religions%20too%2C%20in%20their%20original%20maverick%20forms%20and%20not%20the%20organised%20institutions%20people%20moulded%20them%20into%2C%20began%20with%20questioning%2C%20challenging%20and%20rejecting%20prevalent%20norms.%20Socrates%2C%20Mother%20Lu%2C%20Buddha%2C%20Rabbi%20Akiva%2C%20Jesus%2C%20Mohammad%2C%20Hussain%2C%20Thomas%20Beckett%2C%20Galileo%2C%20Guru%20Arjun%20Dev%2C%20Sojourner%20Truth%2C%20Emily%20Davison%2C%20Jyotirao%20and%20Savitribai%20Phule%2C%20Kanaklata%20Barua%2C%20Gandhi%2C%20Ambedkar%2C%20Martin%20Luther%20King%20and%20other%20such%20men%20and%20women%2C%20some%20remembered%20by%20history%20and%20others%20less%20so%2C%20all%20stood%20up%20and%20said%20no.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20people%2C%20these%20%E2%80%9Cmartyrs%2C%E2%80%9D%20all%20put%20their%20principles%20above%20their%20own%20lives%3B%20%3Cem%3Emartyr%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20ancient%20Greek%2C%20as%20in%20Arabic%2C%20means%20both%20witness%20and%20also%20%E2%80%98she%20who%20lays%20down%20her%20life%20for%20a%20higher%20principle%E2%80%99.%20In%20Hebrew%2C%20the%20word%20for%20martyr%2C%20%3Cem%3Ekaddosh%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20means%20%E2%80%98that%20which%20is%20separated%20and%20becomes%20consecrated%20or%20holy%E2%80%99.%20By%20quite%20literally%20dissolving%20their%20sense%20of%20self%20into%20the%20higher%20principle%20through%20martyrdom%2C%20the%20martyr%20becomes%20consecrated%20and%20bears%20witness%20to%20that%20truth.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20cannot%20all%20be%20martyrs%20but%20we%20can%20all%20be%20witnesses.%20Witnesses%20to%20the%20injustice%20and%20suffering%20in%20the%20world.%20Witnesses%20to%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20power%20and%20wealth%20create%20systems%20to%20perpetuate%20themselves.%20What%20you%20do%2C%20if%20anything%20at%20all%2C%20about%20that%20which%20you%20bear%20witness%20to%20will%20be%20your%20individual%20choice.%20The%20university%20can%20play%20a%20role%20as%20a%20place%20that%20teaches%20you%20to%20recognise%20the%20patterns%20of%20injustice%2C%20the%20deceptions%20of%20power%20and%20the%20frailties%20of%20the%20human%20condition.%20More%20than%20anything%2C%20a%20university%20holds%20up%20the%20mirror%20to%20us%2C%20its%20inhabitants%2C%20and%20also%20to%20society.%20It%20is%20no%20wonder%20then%20that%20universities%20often%20end%20up%20playing%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20political%20changes%2C%20in%20revolutions%3B%20a%20good%20university%20is%20as%20close%20as%20we%20can%20come%20to%20a%20utopia.%20Of%20course%2C%20universities%20themselves%20are%20the%20products%20of%20circumstances%20but%20we%2C%20the%20people%20who%20inhabit%20these%20ivory%20towers%2C%20can%20and%20should%20be%20sentinels%20against%20encroachments%20into%20our%20minds%20and%20our%20classrooms%2C%20regardless%20of%20whether%20these%20threats%20are%20posed%20from%20within%20or%20from%20outside.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Funiversities-future-ruins-excellence%5C%22%3EIn%20Central%20Universities%2C%20the%20Future%20Will%20Now%20Be%20Built%20on%20the%20Ruins%20of%20Excellence%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20world%20where%20it%20is%20easier%20to%20say%20yes%2C%20saying%20no%20requires%20courage%20and%20it%20also%20requires%20clarity.%20It%20requires%20clarity%20about%20defining%20and%20identifying%20justice%20and%20injustice%2C%20clarity%20about%20trying%20to%20alleviate%20pain%20and%20suffering%2C%20clarity%20about%20fighting%20oppression%20and%20persecution%2C%20and%20clarity%20in%20the%20final%20analysis%20about%20who%20we%20are%2C%20what%20we%20want%20and%20what%20we%20hold%20dear.%20A%20good%20education%20should%20help%20us%20to%20gain%20this%20clarity.%20It%20should%20not%20tell%20us%20or%20preach%20to%20us%20but%20should%20give%20us%20the%20tools%20of%20how%20to%20think%2C%20never%20telling%20us%20what%20to%20think.%20It%20should%20help%20us%20to%20ask%20the%20right%20questions%20not%20because%20we%20want%20the%20approval%20of%20others%20but%20because%20we%20want%20to%20improve%20ourselves!%20As%20Master%20Kong-zi%2C%20or%20Confucius%20%E2%80%93%20his%20Latinised%20name%2C%20says%2C%20we%20must%20sit%20still%20and%20meditate%20on%20the%20names%20of%20things.%20We%20must%20then%20name%20things%20with%20their%20corresponding%20reality.%20Most%20of%20the%20time%20we%20use%20language%20to%20cover%20up%2C%20hide%2C%20manipulate%20and%20deceive.%20What%20is%20collateral%20damage%20but%20an%20inane%20phrase%20to%20describe%20the%20murder%20of%20civilians%3F%20How%20many%20other%20words%20are%20there%20which%20hide%20reality%20from%20us%20in%20the%20name%20of%20some%20totem%3F%20How%20many%20such%20words%20do%20we%20use%20to%20mask%20our%20own%20selves%3F%20So%20a%20part%20of%20a%20good%20education%20is%20to%20provide%20you%20the%20tools%20to%20unmask%20such%20deceit!%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnother%20part%20of%20education%20is%20developing%20an%20ethical%20capaciousness%2C%20to%20somehow%20be%20inclusive%20even%20towards%20those%20who%20are%20ostensibly%20excluded.%20Someone%20once%20asked%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fmaulana-hasrat-mohani-muslim-communist%5C%22%3EMaulana%20Hasrat%20Mohani%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20incidentally%20coined%20the%20phrase%20%3Cem%3EInquilab%20Zindabad%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20how%20he%2C%20being%20a%20devout%20Muslim%2C%20could%20be%20a%20founder%20member%20of%20the%20godless%2C%20atheist%20Communist%20Party.%20Mohani%20answered%20and%20said%20why%20do%20you%20worry%20about%20them%3F%20They%20are%20at%20the%20%3Cem%3Emaqaam%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20the%20place%20of%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3ELa%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20and%20eventually%20they%20will%20find%20their%20way!%20His%20allusion%20was%20of%20course%20to%20the%20Muslim%20declaration%20of%20faith%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3ELa%20Ilaaha%20IlalAllah%2C%20Mohammandun%20RasoolAllah%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20begins%20with%20the%20word%20%3Cem%3ELa%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20means%20no!%20Negation%20before%20affirmation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShankaracharya%E2%80%99s%20Advait%2C%20not%20two!%20Of%20course%2C%20the%20Maulana%20made%20light%20of%20a%20serious%20matter%2C%20but%20if%20we%20were%20to%20take%20his%20retort%20seriously%2C%20we%20see%20he%20demonstrates%20an%20ethical%20capaciousness.%20What%20was%20important%20at%20that%20moment%20was%20how%20to%20resolve%20an%20ostensible%20contradiction%2C%20even%20conflict.%20It%20is%20so%20easy%20to%20damn%20each%20other%20but%20much%20harder%20to%20build%20bridges.%20The%20Maulana%20had%203%20holy%20M%E2%80%99s%20which%20he%20held%20dear%3A%20Mecca%2C%20as%20a%20Muslim%2C%20Mathura%20as%20a%20devotee%20of%20Krishna%20Ji%20and%20Moscow%20which%20for%20him%20represented%20a%20political%20model%20of%20equality.%20Today%2C%20Mohani%2C%20who%20said%20%E2%80%98No!%E2%80%99%20to%20signing%20the%20draft%20of%20the%20constitution%20when%20it%20was%20being%20written%20as%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t%20protect%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20disenfranchised%2C%20the%20marginalised%20and%20the%20oppressed%2C%20would%20equally%20frustrate%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ebhakt%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20political%20sense%20and%20not%20the%20real%20sense%2C%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20%E2%80%9Cleft-liberal%20sickulars%E2%80%9D!%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F13144917%2FAmbedkar_and_Maulana_Hasrat_Mohani_at_Sardar_Patels_reception.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Maulana%20Hasrat%20Mohani%20(L)%20with%20Dr%20B.R.%20Ambedkar.%20Credit%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F13144917%2FAmbedkar_and_Maulana_Hasrat_Mohani_at_Sardar_Patels_reception.jpg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F13144917%2FAmbedkar_and_Maulana_Hasrat_Mohani_at_Sardar_Patels_reception-300x194.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F13144917%2FAmbedkar_and_Maulana_Hasrat_Mohani_at_Sardar_Patels_reception-768x497.jpg%20768w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-248579%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22518%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMaulana%20Hasrat%20Mohani%20(L)%20with%20Dr%20B.R.%20Ambedkar.%20Credit%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3ENo%20university%20can%20produce%20a%20Hasrat%20Mohani.%20Neither%20should%20it%20seek%20to%20produce%20Bhagat%20Singhs%2C%20Umar%20Khalids%2C%20or%20for%20that%20matter%20Savarkars%20and%20Tejaswi%20Suryas.%20However%2C%20there%20should%20be%20space%20for%20all%20of%20them%20on%20a%20university%20campus.%20To%20want%20to%20%E2%80%9Cproduce%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20a%20rather%20vulgar%20word%20in%20my%20opinion%20%E2%80%93%20such%20people%20would%20be%20arrogant%20on%20the%20part%20of%20us%20teachers%20and%20would%20deny%20the%20autonomy%20and%20agency%20of%20the%20individuals%20whom%20we%20teach.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20believe%20it%20is%20not%20my%20job%20to%20define%20for%20you%20what%20is%20right%20or%20wrong%2C%20good%20or%20bad%2C%20just%20or%20unjust%20but%20rather%20it%20is%20my%20duty%20to%20equip%20you%20with%20tools%20to%20search%20for%20the%20answers%20to%20these%20questions%20yourself.%20It%20is%20my%20job%20to%20walk%20with%20you%20a%20little%20before%20you%20head%20out%20into%20the%20world%20and%20are%20inundated%20by%20social%20and%20familial%20pressures%2C%20financial%20challenges%20and%20political%20maelstroms%20among%20the%20myriad%20other%20things%20that%20often%20force%20us%20to%20forget%20a%20better%20world%20is%20possible.%20The%20only%20thing%20I%20can%20perhaps%20teach%20you%2C%20then%2C%20is%20how%20important%20it%20is%20to%20say%20no!%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Findia-modi-authoritarianism%5C%22%3ETextbook%20Authoritarianism%20Is%20Playing%20Out%20in%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20must%20realise%20that%20logic%20alone%20can%20never%20help%20us%20reach%20answers%20or%20even%20ask%20the%20right%20questions%3B%20logic%20is%20inevitably%20determined%20by%20the%20limits%20or%20capacities%20of%20our%20minds.%20Logic%20creates%2C%20and%20then%20inhabits%2C%20its%20own%20frameworks.%20But%20as%20we%20know%2C%20%3Cem%3Ekranti%3C%2Fem%3E%20begins%20in%20the%20heart%2C%20not%20necessarily%20in%20%E2%80%9CMind%20and%20Behaviour%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20putting%20principles%20above%20one%E2%80%99s%20own%20life%20ultimately%20requires%20love%2C%20not%20logic.%20Logic%20only%20provides%20signposts%20for%20wayfarers%20on%20the%20path%20of%20truth.%20Love%20provides%20the%20light.%20Without%20love%2C%20logic%20only%20shackles%20the%20mind.%20Logic%20demands%20to%20know%20which%20law%20has%20been%20broken.%20Love%20asks%20who%20has%20been%20hurt%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%20remember%2C%20your%20answers%20must%20come%20from%20within%20you.%20If%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%2C%20they%20will%20remain%20ideas%20that%20have%20not%20germinated%20in%20your%20mind%20but%20rather%20thoughts%20that%20were%20implanted%20there.%20Today%E2%80%99s%20implanted%20beliefs%20and%20ideas%20are%20easily%20supplanted%20tomorrow.%20Our%20duty%20as%20teachers%20is%20to%20plant%20the%20seeds%20of%20critical%20self-reflexivity.%20It%20is%20then%20up%20to%20you%20to%20decide%20whether%20you%20want%20to%20water%20that%20seed%20and%20nourish%20the%20sapling%20so%20it%20can%20become%20a%20tree%20that%20gives%20shade%20to%20you%20and%20others.%20We%20must%20remain%20humble%20enough%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20not%20everyone%20can%20develop%20into%20such%20trees%2C%20but%20we%20all%20do%20need%20their%20shade.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20then%2C%20my%20friends%2C%20is%20this%3A%20are%20we%20ready%20to%20bear%20witness%3F%20Even%20against%20ourselves%3F%20That%20is%20the%20true%20revolution.%20It%20is%20so%20easy%20to%20point%20the%20finger%20at%20others%2C%20mock%20them%20and%20say%20they%20are%20silent%2C%20but%20every%20time%20we%20do%20so%2C%20we%20would%20do%20well%20to%20remember%20Imam%20Ali%E2%80%99s%20saying%20that%20when%20you%20point%20a%20finger%20at%20others%2C%20remember%20three%20fingers%20are%20pointing%20back%20to%20you.%20Ultimately%2C%20an%20overwhelming%20number%20of%20issues%20need%20our%20urgent%20attention%20in%20the%20world.%20A%20good%20education%20will%20perhaps%20help%20you%20unlock%20some%20of%20the%20things%20%3Cem%3Eyou%3C%2Fem%3E%20want%20to%20do%20to%20bring%20about%20change%20for%20the%20better.%20Let%20us%20face%20it%3A%20we%20cannot%20all%20be%20equally%20vocal%20about%20all%20issues.%20Rather%20than%20pointing%20the%20finger%20at%20others%2C%20let%20us%20first%20demand%20critical%20thought%20and%20action%20from%20ourselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fapproaching-gridlock-free-speech-and-failing-democracy%5C%22%3EApproaching%20Gridlock%3A%20Free%20Speech%20and%20Failing%20Democracy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Bertolt%20Brecht%E2%80%99s%20play%2C%20when%20Galileo%20is%20condemned%20for%20heresy%2C%20and%20he%20recants%20his%20beliefs%20in%20heliocentricity%2C%20his%20student%20Andrea%20says%20%E2%80%98Unhappy%20the%20land%20that%20has%20no%20heroes.%E2%80%99%20Galileo%20replies%20and%20says%20%E2%80%98No%2C%20unhappy%20is%20the%20land%20that%20needs%20heroes.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20final%20analysis%2C%20we%20can%20inherit%20many%20things%20from%20our%20parents%2C%20our%20teachers%20or%20even%20from%20previous%20ages%2C%20but%20we%20cannot%20inherit%20their%20spirit.%20So%2C%20as%20Kierkegaard%20says%2C%20%E2%80%98each%20generation%20must%20begin%20anew.%E2%80%99%20Even%20various%20holy%20books%2C%20seemingly%20drawing%20such%20fierce%2C%20even%20fiery%2C%20lines%20between%20believers%20and%20disbelievers%2C%20much%20like%20we%20draw%20lines%20between%20citizens%20and%20others%2C%20caution%20against%20merely%20copying%20what%20our%20predecessors%20did%20without%20thinking%20for%20ourselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%20for%20some%20time%2C%20as%20we%20sojourn%20here%20together%2C%20let%20us%20dare%20to%20ask%20the%20most%20uncomfortable%20questions%2C%20not%20just%20of%20others%20but%20of%20ourselves.%20Let%20us%20revel%20in%20complexity%20and%20contradiction%20and%20leave%20behind%20false%20notions%20of%20authenticity%20and%20certainty.%20Let%20us%20illuminate%20our%20minds%20and%20open%20our%20hearts.%20When%20we%20leave%2C%20we%20will%20remember%20utopia%20is%20not%20just%20a%20physical%20place%20we%20yearn%20for.%20No!%20It%20is%20a%20state%20of%20mind%2C%20it%20is%20the%20heart%20unveiled%20so%20that%20the%20light%20within%20can%20give%20us%20hope%20as%20we%20weather%20the%20storms%20that%20will%20inevitably%20engulf%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAli%20Khan%20Mahmudabad%2C%20associate%20professor%20of%20Political%20Science%20at%20Ashoka%20University%2C%20delivered%20this%20speech%20on%20September%2018%2C%202023%20as%20part%20of%20a%20series%20of%20interdisciplinary%20teach-ins%20on%20academic%20freedom.%20The%20published%20text%20was%20written%20as%20a%20speech%20and%20not%20an%20article.%20Minor%20modifications%20have%20been%20made%20to%20the%20original.%20The%20author%E2%80%99s%20opinions%20are%20his%20own.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.the-edict.in%2Fpost%2Frevolutions-begin-with-no%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20Edict%3Cem%3E%2C%20an%20independent%20student%20newspaper%20covering%20Ashoka%20University%20since%202014.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695781853000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F03213851%2FIMG_2075.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Frevolutions-begin-with-no-and-this-journey-starts-with-asking-questions%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20has%20never%20been%20easy%20to%20ask%20questions%20in%20human%20history.%20Those%20who%20have%20questioned%20have%20been%20persecuted%2C%20hounded%2C%20punished%20and%20even%20killed.%20Science%20has%20progressed%20because%20of%20the%20courage%20people%20had%20to%20say%20no.%20Philosophical%20movements%20and%20religions%2C%20too%2C%20began%20with%20questioning.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Frevolutions-begin-with-no-and-this-jour