s%20found%20stone%20tools%20humans%20used%20to%20butcher%20animals%20in%20what's%20now%20Oregon.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20tools%20were%20below%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffossil-discovery-california-ancient-elephants-camels-dogs-2021-5%5C%22%3Eancient%20camel%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20bison%20tooth%20fragments%20that%20were%20over%2018%2C000%20years%20old.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EIt's%20among%20the%20earliest%20evidence%20of%20human%20occupation%20in%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAncient%20hunters%20used%20a%20rock-shelter%20in%20the%20Oregon%20desert%20to%20butcher%20camels%2C%20bison%2C%20mountain%20sheep%2C%20and%20horses%20during%20the%20Ice%20Age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202012%20and%202015%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faround.uoregon.edu%2Fcontent%2Ffield-site-shows-evidence-humans-oregon-18000-years-ago%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earcheologists%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20blood-stained%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-archaeological-discoveries-of-2015-12%2310000-year-old-stone-tools-used-by-ancient-humans-in-washington-state-6%5C%22%3Estone%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E%20buried%20below%20teeth%20from%20the%20extinct%20animals.%20Recent%20testing%20dates%20the%20teeth%20to%20over%2018%2C000%20years%20old%2C%20and%20the%20tools%20could%20be%20even%20older%2C%20providing%20evidence%20of%20some%20of%20the%20earliest%20human%20occupants%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20we%20think%20that%20the%20site%20was%20occupied%20for%20somewhere%20around%2011%2C000%20years%2C%20between%20about%207%2C000%20and%2018%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20Patrick%20O'Grady%2C%20staff%20archaeologist%20with%20the%20University%20of%20Oregon%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fnatural-history.uoregon.edu%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMuseum%20of%20Natural%20and%20Cultural%20History%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stone%20tools%20were%20below%20fragments%20of%20animal%20teeth%2C%20and%20both%20were%20covered%20by%20volcanic%20ash.%20The%20ash%20landed%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmount-st-helens-lava-2016-12%5C%22%3EMount%20St.%20Helens%3C%2Fa%3E%20erupted%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faround.uoregon.edu%2Fcontent%2Fretooling-prevailing-theories-about-ancient-oregonians%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eover%2015%2C000%20years%20ago%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20teeth%20belonged%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nps.gov%2Farticles%2F000%2Fthe-camels.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECamelops%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20bison%20relative%2C%20both%20extinct%20for%20about%2010%2C000%20years.%20Radiocarbon%20dating%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.blm.gov%2Fpress-release%2Ftesting-yields-new-evidence-human-occupation-18000-years-ago-oregon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erevealed%20the%3C%2Fa%3E%20tooth%20enamel%20to%20be%2018%2C250%20years%20old.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20they%20know%20how%20old%20the%20teeth%20are%2C%20O'Grady%20and%20the%20team%20plan%20to%20publish%20the%20findings%20in%20a%20peer-reviewed%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20tools%20were%20below%20the%20teeth%2C%20the%20researchers%20estimate%20they're%20at%20least%20as%20old%2C%20or%20older%2C%20than%20the%2018%2C250-year-old%20teeth.%20It's%20basically%20like%20if%20you%20were%20to%20try%20and%20date%20the%20laundry%20in%20your%20laundry%20basket%20for%20the%20week%2C%20O'Grady%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20clothes%20you%20tossed%20in%20on%20Monday%20will%20sit%20below%20whatever%20you%20tossed%20in%20on%20Thursday%2C%20as%20long%20as%20no%20one's%20dug%20through%20it%20already%20(or%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20archaeological%20finds%2C%20as%20long%20as%20there%20wasn't%20a%20geological%20shakeup.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20Stone%20Age%20Swiss%20Army%20knife%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20tools%20are%20made%20of%20orange%20chalcedony%2C%20a%20type%20of%20quartz.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20really%20high-quality%20tool%20stone%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Grady%20said.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20away%2C%20O'Grady%20and%20his%20colleagues%20were%20surprised%20to%20find%20that%20type%20of%20stone.%20%26quot%3BIt%20didn't%20look%20familiar%20to%20anybody%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20They%20determined%20the%20stone's%20place%20of%20origin%20was%20at%20least%2050%20to%2075%20miles%20away.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Several%20people%20stand%20near%20the%20Rimrock%20Draw%20Rockshelter%2C%20an%20archeological%20site%20containg%20stone%20tools%20that%20are%20over%2018%2C000%20years%20old%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6513363051acc80019f0da93%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EArtist-in-residence%20Nancy%20Pobanz%20gives%20a%20presentation%20at%20the%20Rimrock%20Draw%20Rockshelter%20archeological%20site.%3Cp%3EPatrick%20O'Grady%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tool%20they%20found%20in%202012%20is%20a%20bit%20smaller%20than%20the%20size%20of%20a%20wallet%20with%20a%20rounded%2C%20rectangular%20shape.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20had%20three%20edges%20that%20had%20different%20kinds%20of%20flaking%20done%20to%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Grady%20said%2C%20a%20curved%20blade%2C%20a%20flatter%20side%2C%20and%20sawtooth%20edge.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20could%20easily%20hold%20the%20thing%20and%20use%20all%20three%20of%20those%20different%20functioning%20edges%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Grady%20said%2C%20like%20a%20multi-purpose%20tool%20or%20Swiss%20Army%20knife.%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20tool%20is%20also%20orange%20chalcedony%20and%20is%20about%203%20inches%20long%20and%20appears%20to%20be%20only%20lightly%20used.%20It%20may%20be%20a%20chipped-off%20piece%20of%20another%20tool.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBison%20blood%20and%20camel%20teeth%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20tested%20the%20multi-tool%20and%20found%20bison%20blood%20on%20it.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmnch.uoregon.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2022-02%2FRDR%2520Synopsis.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENewer%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E%20researchers%20found%20at%20the%20site%20contained%20remnants%20of%20mountain%20sheep%20and%20horse%20blood.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20blood%20and%20many%20camel%20and%20bison%20teeth%20fragments%20suggest%20people%20used%20the%20site%20as%20a%20place%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F300000-year-old-schoeningen-marking-early-prehistoric-clothing-bear-skin-2023-1%5C%22%3Ebutcher%20animals%3C%2Fa%3E%20instead%20of%20as%20a%20full-time%20residence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20camp%20that%20people%20came%20to%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20and%20especially%20when%20they%20were%20hunting%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Grady%20said.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221130%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tooth%20enamel%20from%20a%20camelops%2C%20an%20ancient%20camel%20ancestor%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6513379851acc80019f0daec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22846%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20of%20the%20tooth%20enamel%20found%20at%20the%20Rimrock%20Draw%20Rockshelter%20is%20over%2018%2C000%20years%20old.%3Cp%3EThomas%20W.%20Stafford%2C%20Jr.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Rimrock%20Draw%20Rockshelter%2C%20where%20the%20tools%20were%20found%2C%20is%20a%2065-foot%20cleft%20in%20a%20basalt%20rim%20near%20an%20ancient%2C%20now-dry%20stream.%20There%20could%20be%20more-permanent%20dwellings%20in%20the%20area%20archaeologists%20have%20yet%20to%20find.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20oldest%20evidence%20of%20humans%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20experts%20believed%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeople-in-north-america-15000-years-earlier-than-archaeologists-thought-2020-7%5C%22%3EClovis%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20the%20first%20humans%20in%20North%20America%2C%20having%20crossed%20the%20Bering%20land%20bridge%20from%20Siberia%20to%20Canada%2013%2C000%20years%20ago.%20But%20recent%20discoveries%20have%20indicated%20a%20pre-Clovis%20culture%20that's%20thousands%20of%20years%20older.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOregon%20and%20surrounding%20states%20contain%20some%20of%20the%20oldest%20evidence%20of%20ancient%20human%20habitation%20in%20the%20US.%20Coopers%20Ferry%2C%20in%20Idaho%2C%20is%20about%20240%20miles%20to%20the%20northeast%20of%20Rimrock%20Draw.%20Its%20storage%20pits%20and%20evidence%20of%20animal%20consumption%20date%20to%20about%2016%2C000%20years%20ago.%20Paisley%20Cave%2C%20about%2075%20miles%20away%20from%20Rimrock%2C%20has%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faround.uoregon.edu%2Fcontent%2Fpaisley-caves-study-uncovers-new-scoop-ancient-poop%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E14%2C400-year-old%3C%2Fa%3E%20preserved%20human%20excrement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20still%20a%20lot%20to%20learn%20about%20how%20humans%20arrived%20and%20dispersed%20throughout%20North%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiscoveries-changed-understanding-human-history-evolution-2020-12%23another-study-of-the-earliest-americans-showed-that-females-played-a-role-hunting-big-game-7%5C%22%3ESouth%20America%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BWe%20just%20don't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20evidence%20going%20back%20that%20far%20in%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Grady%20said.%20But%20he%20thinks%20it's%20only%20a%20matter%20of%20time%20before%20someone%20finds%20even%20older%20evidence%20of%20human%20occupation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20very%20exciting%20time%20to%20be%20doing%20archaeology%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bhaving%20one%20site%20that's%20pretty%20old%20right%20now%20and%20could%20be%20superseded%20by%20another%20one%20in%20no%20time%20at%20all.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feighteen-thousand-year-old-stone-tools-among-oldest-found-us-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695763940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651337b651acc80019f0dafe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feighteen-thousand-year-old-stone-tools-among-oldest-found-us-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ancient%20hunters%20butchered%20extinct%20camels%20and%20bison%20in%20what's%20now%20Oregon%20over%2018%2C000%20years%20ago.%20Archeologists%20found%20stone%20tools%2C%20blood%2C%20and%20teeth.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jmcgrath%40insider.com%20(Jenny%20McGrath)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A87%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feighteen-thousand-year-old-stone-tools-among-oldest-found-us-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UPS%20says%20it%20will%20hire%20100%2C000%20seasonal%20workers%20for%20the%20holiday%20rush%20%E2%80%94%20but%20don't%20expect%20that%20%24170%2C000%20pay%20package%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222644%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20UPS%20semi-truck.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6513301851acc80019f0d91c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221983%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUPS%20said%20it%20will%20hire%20100%2C000%20seasonal%20workers%20for%20the%20holiday%20rush.%3Cp%3EScott%20Olson%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EUPS%20plans%20on%20hiring%20100%2C000%20seasonal%20workers%20to%20beef%20up%20its%20workforce%20for%20the%20holiday%20