%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F326173%2Forigins-of-iconic-indian-dishes-loved-across-the-world-food-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20bread%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20cooked%20by%20placing%20a%20cross%20made%20from%20the%20palm%20leaf%20received%20on%20Palm%20Sunday.%20In%20the%20evening%2C%20the%20male%20head%20of%20the%20family%20breaks%20the%20bread%20after%20prayers%20and%20shares%20it%20with%20his%20family%20to%20commemorate%20the%20Last%20Supper.%20The%20bread%20is%20eaten%20with%20a%20jaggery%20sauce%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20book%20notes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E3.%20Ariputtu%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%2015th%20century%20when%20the%20Portuguese%20entered%20Kerala%2C%20they%20brought%20with%20them%20spices%2C%20potatoes%2C%20chillies%2C%20etc.%20One%20of%20the%20foods%20they%20%E2%80%9Cinvented%E2%80%9D%2C%20shares%20Tanya%20in%20her%20book%2C%20was%20the%20%3Cem%3Eputtu%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20steamed%20rice%20cake).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20talks%20of%20how%20the%20%3Cem%3Eputtu%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20originally%20made%20in%20bamboo%20steamers%20or%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F325105%2Fhyderabad-entrepreneur-raju-bhupati-makes-affordable-troo-good-millet-snacks%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecoconut%20shells%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20has%20now%20shifted%20to%20more%20user-friendly%20metal%20%3Cem%3Eputtu%3C%2Fem%3E-makers.%20In%20contrast%20to%20the%20previously%20used%20%3Cem%3Eoralus%20%3C%2Fem%3E(granite%20tools)%2C%20mill-ground%20rice%20is%20now%20used.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E4.%20Chemeen%20Pada%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shrimp%20pickle%2C%20a%20staple%20in%20Tanya%E2%80%99s%20household%2C%20is%20an%20ode%20to%20the%20Portuguese%20tradition%20of%20pickling%20meats%20in%20vinegar.%20In%20fact%2C%20as%20Tanya%20writes%2C%20vinegar%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20foods%20brought%20to%20Kerala%20during%20the%20colonisation%20in%20the%2015th%20century.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Portuguese%20used%20vinegar%20extensively%20in%20their%20food%3B%20especially%20to%20preserve%20salted%20meats%20with%20paprika%20and%20garlic%20which%20were%20stored%20in%20large%20barrels%20during%20their%20voyages%20in%20ships%20to%20lands%20afar.%20This%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20quick%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F324582%2Fshashikala-sanadhya-gives-indian-food-cooking-lessons-for-foreign-tourists-in-udaipur%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esavouring%20dish%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20fried%20in%20oil%2C%20close%20to%20the%20meat%20pickle%20famously%20relished%20in%20Kerala%20today.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E5.%20Kazhal%20Kothiyathu%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Latin%20Catholic%20minced%20liver%20fry%20recipe%20prepared%20by%20Tanya%E2%80%99s%20grandmother%20differs%20from%20other%20community%20recipes%20in%20terms%20of%20preparation.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20not%20unusual%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Tanya%2C%20who%20noticed%20how%20cooking%20styles%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F322885%2Fkarnataka-shivaranjini-started-suggi-oota-south-indian-restaurant-in-california%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecipes%3C%2Fa%3E%20differed%20across%20catholic%20communities%20even%20within%20Kerala%20itself.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20choppers%20were%20not%20available%2C%20quick%20and%20constant%20chopping%20of%20the%20meat%20on%20a%20large%20wooden%20board%20(with%20two%20knives%20on%20either%20hand)%20was%20how%20the%20liver%20was%20minced%20to%20a%20fine%20form.%20A%20task%20that%20required%20not%20only%20strength%20but%20also%20precision%2C%E2%80%9D%20notes%20the%20book.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E6.%20Dutch%20bread%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FC0LTv7CUUAEWuw0-1694788427.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Breudher%20a%20Dutch%20speciality%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FC0LTv7CUUAEWuw0-1694788427.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FC0LTv7CUUAEWuw0-1694788427-300x231.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FC0LTv7CUUAEWuw0-1694788427-500x384.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FC0LTv7CUUAEWuw0-1694788427-768x590.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FC0LTv7CUUAEWuw0-1694788427-150x115.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-330130%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22922%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EBreudher%20a%20Dutch%20speciality%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20X%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FBreadTalkSL%2Fstatus%2F811443707379650560%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBreadTalk%20Sri%20Lanka%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bread%20known%20as%20%E2%80%98bluder%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98brudel%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98blueda%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98bloeder%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98blueda%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20remnant%20of%20the%20Dutch%20rule%20in%20the%2017th%20century.%20It%20amassed%20immense%20popularity%20as%20a%20culinary%20gem%20and%20is%20still%20enjoyed%20centuries%20after%20the%20Dutch%20rule%20ended%20in%20Kochi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrepared%20with%20maida%2C%20sugar%2C%20eggs%2C%20ghee%20and%20yeast%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F321953%2Flist-of-eight-iconic-irani-cafes-in-mumbai-britannia-kyani-yazdani-ideal-corner%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20bread%20%3C%2Fa%3Ealso%20features%20raisins%20in%20rare%20cases.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20said%20that%20the%20raisins%20do%20not%20sink%20to%20the%20bottom%20in%20a%20breudher%20made%20well%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tanya%20writes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E7.%20Neiappam%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Jewish%20community%20entered%20Kerala%20in%20the%2015th%20and%2016th%20centuries%20from%20Spain%20and%20Portugal%2C%20bringing%20their%20food%20along%20with%20them.%20In%20the%20book%2C%20Tanya%20writes%20that%20it%20was%20due%20to%20the%20Portuguese%20tyranny%20that%20they%20fled%20to%20Kochi%20and%20thrived%20in%20Jew%20Town%20in%20Mattancherry.%20While%20today%2C%20only%20vestiges%20of%20the%20Malabari%20synagogues%20are%20present%20in%20Kerala%2C%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F319669%2Fbengaluru-family-starts-traditional-south-indian-food-stall-business-in-brooklyn-swetha-raju%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20the%20culinary%20legacy%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethey%20left%20behind%20is%20still%20prevalent.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Eispethi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(red%20beef%20stew)%20and%20%3Cem%3Eneiappam%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20breakfast%20or%20tea%20time%20snack%2C%20which%20the%20Jews%20especially%20prepare%20during%20Hannukah%20as%20a%20popular%20treat%20during%20the%20festival%2C%20%3Cem%3Eneiappam%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20popular%20across%20Kerala%20and%20also%20called%20%3Cem%3Eunniyappam%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20book%20mentions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694844000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FScreenshot_20230915-172153_Kindle-1694787839.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.